Yes the new image also doesnâ€™t run on M1.
For now to unblock everyone, if you want to run rabbitmq locally you can follow following steps:
1. Checkout to commit before rabbitmq change (change commit (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/commits/716ee949db80f5fbdeee5289b98b35ff3eaf0d0b/), commit (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/commits/4bf13c08aff30aa6d729ee13e86461df00c49f7d) just before that), make before this you commit / stash all your changes
```git checkout 4bf13c08aff30aa6d729ee13e86461df00c49f7d```
2. Build rabbitmq image, this will build instabase/rabbitmq image on your local system
```python provisioner.py compile rabbitmq```
3. Checkout back to you branch
```git checkout <your-working-branch>```
4. Start rabbitmq by using with prebuilt flag
```python provisioner.py start rabbitmq --use-prebuilt```
I will look into this in more detail soon, till then above steps should work

FYI in case anyone else is having trouble running services locally and would like to make the shift to developing on Crafting
